## Dependencies & Blocking Relationships

### Critical Path (Longest blocking chain)
1. PLAN-001 (create .prd) 
2. ENHANCE-001, ENHANCE-002, ENHANCE-003, ENHANCE-004, ENHANCE-005, ENHANCE-006, ENHANCE-007 (all parallel, but all required)
3. ENHANCE-008 (merge all 7)
4. SYMLINK-001 + VALIDATE-001 (parallel after merge)
5. GIT-001 (final push, all prior must complete)

**Total duration**: ~9 hours (with parallel execution)

### Parallel Execution Opportunities
- **Wave 2a**: ENHANCE-001, ENHANCE-002, ENHANCE-003 can run simultaneously
- **Wave 2b**: ENHANCE-004, ENHANCE-005, ENHANCE-006 can run simultaneously  
- **Wave 3**: ENHANCE-007 can run in parallel with Wave 2a/2b
- **Wave 4**: SYMLINK-001 and VALIDATE-001 can run simultaneously after ENHANCE-008
- **Total serialization**: PLAN-001 → (all ENHANCE parallel) → ENHANCE-008 → (SYMLINK+VALIDATE parallel) → GIT-001

### Blocking Rules
- Nothing can proceed until PLAN-001 completes (defines all work)
- ENHANCE-008 cannot start until all 7 ENHANCE items complete (needs all input)
- GIT-001 cannot start until SYMLINK-001 AND VALIDATE-001 complete (gates on validation)

